data.title: Review of 2020 Presidential Election voting trends in Northwestern Township of Elgin: Precinct Elgin 15
data.meta_description: With less than 12 months until the 2024 U.S. Presidential Election, a Kane County Reporter analysis of Illinois voter history data shows 915 voters in Northwestern Township of Elgin: Precinct Elgin 15 cast ballots four years ago, in 2020.
data.text:
As we approach the 2024 U.S. Presidential Election, a review of the 2020 voting patterns in Northwestern Township of Elgin: Precinct Elgin 15 can provide valuable insights. In the contest between Donald J. Trump and Joe Biden, 915 of the 1,101 residents cast their ballots, resulting in an 83.1% turnout, according to the Illinois State Board of Elections.

The voting breakdown in Northwestern Township of Elgin: Precinct Elgin 15 reveals 44.2% of the total supporting Republicans, and 54.5% of the votes for Democrats, highlighting the precinct's political preferences.

Overall, 186 registered voters in Northwestern Township of Elgin: Precinct Elgin 15 did not vote in 2020.

Additionally, an estimated total of 1,478 residents were reported to be aged 18 or older in Northwestern Township of Elgin: Precinct Elgin 15, according to the last US Census and the 2021 American Community Survey.

The Illinois State Board of Elections ensures the integrity and security of the electoral process in Illinois. They handle candidate certifications, vote tallying, and campaign disclosures. Following a significant cyberattack in 2016, the board also focuses on bolstering electoral cybersecurity. Governed by the Illinois Election Code (10 ILCS 5), the SBE is committed to conducting fair and transparent elections.
